    "minides": "The original luxury performance SUV — now in its third generation with a Taycan-inspired triple-screen interior, air suspension as standard, Matrix LED headlamps, and a 4.0L V8 in the range-topping GTS.",
    "description": "The Porsche Cayenne is the original luxury performance SUV and Porsche's best-selling model globally. Offered in India in two variants — the Cayenne (V6) at ₹1.51 crore and the GTS (V8) at ₹1.83 crore — both come as fully imported (CBU) units. The standard Cayenne uses a 3.0-litre twin-turbocharged V6 producing 353 PS and 500 Nm, while the GTS steps up to a 4.0-litre twin-turbo V8 with 500 PS and 660 Nm along with a standard sport exhaust, GTS-specific chassis tuning, Porsche Torque Vectoring Plus (PTV+), and rear-axle steering. Both share an 8-speed Tiptronic S, Porsche Traction Management AWD, PASM adaptive suspension, and air suspension as standard for India. The Taycan-inspired cabin features a 12.3-inch PCM touchscreen, 12.6-inch curved digital cluster, optional 10.9-inch co-driver screen, 4-zone climate control, and 8-way electric front seats. HD Matrix LEDs with 64,000 pixels are standard on the GTS. The Cayenne's Bespoke personalisation catalogue makes virtually every aspect configurable at additional cost."
  },
